<h1>SwiftSharing Privacy Policy</h1>
<small>Last Updated: March 18, 2011</small>
<h2>This Policy Covers</h2>
<p>This policy covers how SwiftSharing.net treats information that SwiftSharing.net collects and receives, including information related to your past use of SwiftSharing.net products and services. This policy does not apply to the practices of companies that SwiftSharing.net does not own or control (including, but not limited to, advertisers), or to people that SwiftSharing.net does not employ or pay. </p>
<h2>Use of Information Collected</h2>
<p>SwiftSharing gains information when you register with SwiftSharing, when you use SwiftSharing products or services, and when you visit SwiftSharing pages. SwiftSharing may collect information about you and your use of the website that is both personal and non-personal. For purposes of this policy, "personal information" is information about you that can be used to personally identify you, such as your email address, and that is not otherwise publicly available. "Non-personal" information is everything else. 

When you register to use SwiftSharing we ask for information such as your e-mail address, birth date, gender, etc. Once you register with SwiftSharing and sign in to our services, you are not anonymous to us. 

SwiftSharing may also collect information about your transactions with us and your transactions with our business affiliates, vendors, and advertisers, including information about your use of products offered through the website. SwiftSharing may also collect information about you from other sources, such as blogs and instant messaging services, and other users of SwiftSharing services. SwiftSharing automatically receives and records information on our server logs from your browser, including your IP address, SwiftSharing cookie information (including without limitation cookies, flash cookies, and beacons), and the pages you request. SwiftSharing may use some or all of your information for the following general purposes:
<span></span>To customize your experience,
<span></span>To customize the content you see,
<span></span>To fulfill your requests for products and services,
<span></span>To offer customized features,
<span></span>To improve our services,
<span></span> and To contact you.
SwiftSharing securely guards all content you post on the site and it is not vulneralbe to hackers or sold to vendors. 
</p>
